  "title": "Assistant Operations Manager (Ship Agency)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Manage daily tanker port call operations from pre-arrival to post-departure.</li><li>Supervise, coach, and allocate work for a team of operations staff.</li><li>Act as escalation point for operational issues, delays, and client concerns.</li><li>Coordinate with terminals, port authorities, pilots, and service providers.</li><li>Ensure compliance with HSSE, ISGOTT, MARPOL, and port regulations.</li><li>Monitor operational performance, documentation, and cost control.</li><li>Support process improvements and operational reporting.</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Maritime Studies, Shipping, or related field.</li><li>5–8 years of ship agency experience, with strong tanker exposure.</li><li>Prior supervisory or assistant managerial experience preferred.</li><li>Strong leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Ability to perform in a fast-paced, 24/7 operations environment.</li></ul>",
